column2: Being able to assist our customers, especially during this challenging time, has always been of utmost importance for us at AIA Philam Life. With our hotlines and customer service centers temporarily suspended due to the enhanced community quarantine, we‚Äôve gathered your frequently asked questions regarding our services to still help you with your concerns. CLICK on the images below to learn more.

column2: Train like a Spartan even at home! Join the daily virtual workouts of our Spartan Ambassadors -- live on Instagram! Check out the schedule below. Live a healthier, longer, better life with #PhilamVitality! Visit this link to find out more: http://bit.ly/PLVitality

We have partnered with Bayanihan Musikahan and Puhon: Ben&Ben to deliver PPES, test kits and transportation to those who need it the most. We are also supporting food security programs for those who have lost their capacity to earn. In doing so, we feel that we are able to fulfill our mission of helping Filipinos race against risk to live a healthier, longer, better life. We invite you to participate and give what you can to those who need it the most. Let us all do what we can to #FlattenTheCurve!

We also put the spotlight on some of the remarkable WoMen@AXA through an exhibit that recognizes their strength of character, dedication to their profession, and their passion and purpose.  In photo: Peachy and Zaida are exemplary examples of women of strength, character and integrity. Peachy is married, a mother of three and a breast cancer survivor. Zaida is a single, independent woman that loves her furbabies. Peachy is a training and development professional, and Zaida is a certified internal auditor. Both of them excel in their chosen fields and lead fulfilling lives with work-life harmony.

Being tested for the coronavirus and staying in the hospital can have significant financial consequences. Check your InLife policy if you have the I-Heal plan, a Lazada Premium Protect plan, or any individual life insurance plan with a hospitalization benefit (rider) attached to it. If you do, you may claim a daily hospitalization allowance if confinement is due to COVID-19 - based on your policy‚Äôs contract provisions. We want to help you focus on your recovery and relieve your loved ones of any more worry.

column2: With the growing concern about COVID-19 and FWD's continuing commitment to care for customers, FWD is providing existing plan holders ‚ÄúFWD COVID-19 Ready,‚Äù  an additional lump sum medical and funeral benefit if diagnosed with COVID-19, at no extra cost. This benefit is provided on top of eligible and active FWD insurance plans and riders. In addition, for customers who are diagnosed with COVID-19, FWD will be extending payment grace period to 90 days and releasing the FWD COV...ID-19 Ready medical benefit claims within 48 hours. Ask your financial advisor for details or contact our 24/7 LiveChat at fwd.com.ph and on our mobile app, FWD Tapp. Learn more at bit.ly/FWDCOVID19Ready Benefit is available for active and eligible life insurance plans issued up to Feb 29, 2020, except group insurance plans, KanDuu (KanMend, KanLive, and KanGuard), Set Ka Na, and Peace. Coverage period until April 15. #FWDCOVID19Ready

column2: At FWD, our vision is to change the way people feel about insurance. We listen to you and work tirelessly to redefine insurance through your eyes.  When we assist you, we go above and beyond to put ourselves in your shoes first.  We want to give you the protection you need through easy-to-understand products, supported by digital technology. We focus on your other needs as much as your financial ones. We continue to innovate to provide you the best service‚Äîquick, easy, and hassle-free.    We‚Äôre here for you when you need us. We became the first insurance company in the Philippines to offer 24/7 customer service and launched Tapp, our one-tap insurance app, that allows you to manage your plans at the touch of your fingers. We want you to celebrate living without fear because we always have your back.

Driving in the Philippines means you‚Äôll spend countless hours stuck in heavy traffic. It‚Äôs the reality. With this, always assume that most people are in a sour mood already and their patience is wearing thin by the minute. Refrain from doing anything aggressive that will only add fuel to the fire. Maintain the proper speed and observe adequate space for lane changes. If a motorist is tailgating you, move over and let them go. Remember: It isn‚Äôt worth causing an accident or serious injury, just to prove you‚Äôre right. If you expect disciplined driving from others, start with yourself. #FWDMCX #RoadToProgress #GetReadyToLive

column2: If you‚Äôre trying to stick to a budget, it‚Äôs better to shop without the direct or indirect influence (aka peer pressure) from others. The ‚Äúdangers‚Äù are obvious: buying something you don‚Äôt like or won‚Äôt use or can‚Äôt afford just because someone said it was nice on you. Just think of the things you‚Äôre actually saving and how sticking to your budget will get you closer to getting that.  #GetReadyToLive #FWDFinancialSelfCareTip

Breast cancer may not be preventable, but it has a high survival rate and surgeries (like a lumpectomy and mastectomy) are viable options for treatment. A breast cancer diagnosis is life-changing, but the right mindset backed by the proper financial protection can definitely help you in your fight. #GetRadyToLive #FWDPlanWithPurpose

column2: Your vehicle‚Äôs horn should only be used when necessary and not just because you want to make noise and express annoyance to another motorist. If you can help it, don‚Äôt show displeasure to other drivers, minimizing the risk of getting into an altercation or road rage accident. No matter how many times you press your horn, it will not make traffic go faster, so best to have your hands useful on the wheel or gear stick. Listen to music or even meditate to calm yourself. #FWDMCX #RoadToProgress #GetReadyToLive

column2: [UPDATE] Because we heard you! Due to some of your concerns on downloading Pru Life UK‚Äôs health app, Pulse, the launch date of the FREE COVID-19 insurance & personal accident coverage will be moved to April 13. Those who have downloaded the app will receive an in-app notification, so don‚Äôt forget to log in to your account! ---- Starting April 11, leading life insurer Pru Life UK will offer free COVID-19 protection and Personal Accident (PA) coverage to safeguard Filipinos amid the coronavirus outbreak in the country. Under the program, Pru Life UK will offer free accident and death benefit to 500,000 Filipinos, in the unfortunate event that the individual passes away, including as a result of COVID-19. Health workers are entitled to twice the death coverage at no cost. This offer is available through Pulse, Pru Life UK‚Äôs artificial intelligence-powered health and wellness app that offers holistic health management.  Click link to read full story. #WeDoHealth

Download Pulse now for FREE on Google Play Store or Apple App Store: https://wedopulseph.page.link/5dT1

column2: Due to local government guidelines to manage the COVID-19 health emergency across the country, our business centers in Iloilo and Tacloban are temporarily close...d until further notice. In addition, our Davao business centers will also cease operations effective Thursday, March 26. Offices in Luzon will remain closed. Our live customer service will not be available until further notice. Customers may reach out to their financial advisors for any concern on their policies. Alternatively, customers may review and manage their policies through customer portal PRUAccess at https://pruaccess.prulifeuk.com.ph/ or email PRU Customer Action Team at contact.us@prulifeuk.com.ph. We continue to assess and release more timely announcements as the local authorities implement further measures and guidelines.

In achieving your health goals, make sure you know your body well. Keep a good eye on what you really need to address.  Then break it down into smaller attainable goals so you won't get overwhelmed and to always keep you motivated. Take down notes and then assess which works and which doesn‚Äôt.
